arXiv:2409.02460v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: Employing dipole and exponential hadronic transition form factors and helicity analysis combined with the Lattice QCD input, we present a detailed study of the decays $B_s 	o D_s^{(*)}\ell 
u_\ell$. $B_s 	o D_s + P(V)$, where $P = \pi^+, K^+, D_s^+$ and $V = ho^+, K^{*+}, D_s^{*+}$, are also investigated and their branching fractions are examined. At the large recoil point, we calculate $f_{ + ,0}^{{B_s} 	o {D_s}}(0) = 0.67 \pm 0.01$ for both parameterizations. Then we evaluate the branching fractions $BR({B_s} 	o {D_s}\ell 
u )$ and $BR({B_s} 	o {D_s}\ell 
u )$, which leads to $R({D_s}) = 0.298 \pm 0.123$. The ratios $ rac{{\Gamma (B_s^0 	o D_s^ - {\mu ^ + }{
u _\mu })}}{{\Gamma (B_s^0 	o D_s^{* - }{\mu ^ + }{
u _\mu })}}$ are found to be $0.4415 \pm 0.1860$ and $0.4406 \pm 0.1854$, which are in good agreement of recent LHCb collaboration measurement. We also calculate the physical observables, $A_{FB}^\ell ,P_L^\ell ,P_T^\ell ,C_F^\ell ,F_L^\ell $.
